/05/19/monday-final-ratings-stalker-mike-molly-dancing-with-the-stars-adjusted-up/406024/|title=Monday Final Ratings: 'Stalker', 'Mike & Molly' & 'Dancing With the Stars' Adjusted Up|last=Kondolojy|first=Amanda|work=TV by the Numbers|date=May 19, 2015|accessdate=May 19, 2015}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = Beth, Jack, Vicki and the rest of the TAU team continue their search for a serial killer, and Vicki learns some startling information about her ex-husband.\n |LineColor       = 5A5953\n}}\n}}\n\n== Critical reception ==\n''Stalker'' received negative reviews from critics. The [[review aggregator]] [[Rotten Tomatoes]] reported that 20% of critics have given the film a positive review based on 49 reviews, with an [[average rating]] of 3.19/10. The site's critics consensus reads, \"''Stalker'' is chock full of perverted subjects and ugly storylines, making it hard to watch even for those who like to watch.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/stalker/s01 |title=Stalker: Season 1 |publisher=[[Rotten Tomatoes]] |accessdate=January 11, 2020}}</ref> Maureen Ryan of ''[[The Huffington Post]]'' called it \"exploitative, misogynist trash\".<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/09/17/fall-tv-guide_n_5837268.html |title=Fall TV Guide: New Dramas to Follow and Shows to Skip |first=Maureen |last=Ryan |date=17 September 2014 |work=[[The Huffington Post]] |accessdate=2 October 2014}}</ref> At [[Metacritic]], the series premiere garnered a score of 17 out of 100 based on 24 critics, indicating \"overwhelming dislike\". The show also received negative reviews from ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'', ''[[USA Today]]'', and ''[[The A.V. Club]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/tv/stalker |title=Stalker - TV Show Reviews |publisher=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=October 4, 2014}}</ref>\n\n===Awards and nominations===\n\nIn 2015, ''Stalker''{{'}}s [[Dylan McDermott]] was nominated for a [[41st People's Choice Awards|People's Choice Award]] for Favorite Actor in a New TV Series.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/news/peoples-choice-awards-2015-hosts-nominees-announced/|title=People's Choice Awards 2015 hosts, nominees announced|date=4 November 2014|publisher=|accessdate=4 November 2014}}</ref>\n\n=== Ratings ===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:25%;\" rowspan=\"2\"| Time slot ([[Eastern Time Zone (North America)|ET]])\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:7%;\" rowspan=\"2\"| No. of<br />episodes\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=2| Premiered\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=2| Ended\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:7%;\" rowspan=\"2\"| TV Season\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:8%; background:#ffdead;\" rowspan=\"2\"| Rank\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:8%; background:#ffdead;\" rowspan=\"2\"| Ratings\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:8%; background:#ffdead;\" rowspan=\"2\"| Viewers<br />{{nobold|{{small|(in millions)}}}}\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Date\n! scope=\"col\" span style=\"width:8%; line-height:100%;\"| Viewers<br />{{nobold|{{small|(in millions)}}}}\n! scope=\"col\" | Date\n! scope=\"col\" span style=\"width:8%; line-height:100%;\"| Viewers<br />{{nobold|{{small|(in millions)}}}}\n|-\n| span style=\"font-weight:normal;line-height:100%\" |  Wednesday 10:00&nbsp;p.m.<br/><small>(October 1, 2014 \u2013 February 18, 2015)</small><br/>Monday 9:00&nbsp;p.m.<br/><small>(April 27, 2015 \u2013 May 18, 2015)</small>\n| <small>20</small>\n| style=\"font-size:11px;line-height:110%\"| October 1, 2014\n| 9.05<ref name=\"ep1ratings\"/>\n| style=\"font-size:11px;line-height:110%\"| May 18, 2015\n| 6.79<ref name=\"s1finale\"/>\n| style=\"font-size:smaller\"| [[2014\u201315 United States network television schedule|2014\u201315]]\n| style=\"background:#fc9;\"| #43\n| style=\"background:#fc9;\"| 2.3\n| style=\"background:#fc9;\" | 10.13\n|}\n\n==Broadcast==\n''Stalker'' was picked up by several broadcasters outside the United States. The Belgian station Vier airs ''Stalker'' as well every Sunday night as a part of their crime night. In South Africa, the series premiered on October 22, 2014, and airs on [[M-Net|M-Net Edge]] on Wednesdays.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mnet.dstv.com/shows/stalker/|title=Stalker <nowiki>|</nowiki> M-Net|publisher=M-Net|accessdate=October 22, 2014}}</ref> It premiered in the [[UK and Ireland]] on November 10, 2014, on [[Sky Living]] and airs on Mondays. In Romania, it airs every Wednesday on Diva.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sky.com/tv/show/stalker/|title=Sky Living Page for 'Stalker'|publisher=Sky Living|accessdate=January 22, 2015|date=January 22, 2015}}</ref> In New Zealand the series premiered on [[TVNZ]] on January 12, 2015.<ref>{{cite web|title=Stalker|url=http://tvnz.co.nz/stalker/index-group-6195865|website=TVNZ|publisher=Television New Zealand Limited|accessdate=14 April 2015}}</ref> The series premiered in [[Australia]] on [[Nine Network]] on April 12, 2015.<ref name=\"NineApr\">{{cite web|publisher=[[TV Tonight]]|first=David|last=Knox|url=http://www.tvtonight.com.au/2015/04/airdate-almost-human-believe-returning-the-following.html|title=Airdate: Almost Human, Believe. Returning: The Following.|date=April 7, 2015|accessdate=April 7, 2015}}</ref> The show also airs in [[France]], on [[TF1]].  In [[Japan]], ''Stalker'' is shown on cable/satellite channel [[AXN]]. In [[Greece]], the series premiered on September 2016, on [[:el:Star Channel|Star Channel]].\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|3560094}}\n\n{{Kevin Williamson}}\n\n[[Category:2010s American crime drama television series]]\n[[Category:2014 American television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2015 American television series endings]]\n[[Category:American thriller television series]]\n[[Category:CBS original programming]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Fictional portrayals of the Los Angeles Police Department]]\n[[Category:American police procedural television series]]\