{"title_page": "Laura Tesoro", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2017}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name Andr\u00e9 Felipe               = Laura Tesoro\n| image               = ESC2016 - Belgium Meet & Greet 14 (crop).jpg\n| caption             = Tesoro in 2016\n| image_size          = <!-- Only for images narrower than 220 pixels -->\n| background          = solo_singer\n| birth_name          =\n| alias               = \n| birth_date          = {{birth date and age|1996|8|19|df=yes}}\n| birth_place         = [[Antwerp]], Belgium\n| origin              = \n| instrument          = Vocals\n| genre               = {{hlist|[[Pop music|Pop]]|[[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]|[[Funk music|funk]]|[[Dance music|dance]]}}\n| occupation          = {{hlist|Singer|actress}}\n| years_active        = 2008\u2013present\n| label               =\n| associated_acts     = {{hlist|[[Koen Wauters]]}}\n| website             = \n}}\n\n'''Laura Tesoro''' (born 19 August 1996) is a Belgian singer and actress. She represented [[Belgium in the Eurovision Song Contest 2016]] with the song \"[[What's the Pressure]]\".  Tesoro is also known for portraying Charlotte on the Flemish soap opera ''[[Familie]]'', and placing second on [[The Voice van Vlaanderen (season 3)|season three]] of ''[[The Voice van Vlaanderen]]''. The singer is also one of the four coaches on ''[[The Voice Kids (Belgian TV series))]]''\n\n==Biography==\n\n===1996\u20132014: Early life and career beginnings===\nTesoro was born on 19 August 1996 in [[Antwerp]] to an Italian father and a Belgian mother.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://mobile.twitter.com/Lauwraaaaah_/status/563378079004131328?p=v|title= I am Belgian but my father is Italian|accessdate= 9 March 2016|author= Tesoro, Laura|date= 5 February 2015|publisher= [[Twitter]]}}</ref> She had her first acting role in the Flemish crime drama ''[[Witse]]'' as Evy Cuypers in 2008, and went on to perform in musicals such as ''[[Annie (musical)|Annie]]'' and ''Domino''. She performed at [[Ketnetpop]] in 2009. From 2012 to 2014, she appeared as Charlotte in ''[[Familie]]'', a love interest to Guido. In 2014 she appeared in [[The Voice van Vlaanderen (season 3)|season three]] of ''[[The Voice van Vlaanderen]]'', where she ended up as the runner-up. Throughout her time on the show, she was a member of Team [[Koen Wauters|Koen]]. She released her debut single \"[[Outta Here (Laura Tesoro song)|Outta Here]]\" the same year, which peaked at number 23 on the Belgian Flemish Singles Chart.\n\n===2015\u2013present: Eurovision Song Contest===\n{{Main|Belgium in the Eurovision Song Contest 2016}}\nIn 2015, she released her second single \"[[Funky Love (song)|Funky Love]]\". In November 2015, Tesoro was announced as one of the five participants of [[Belgium in the Eurovision Song Contest 2016|''Eurosong 2016'']].<ref>{{citeweb|first=Gil|last=Laufer|url=http://esctoday.com/106766/belgium-national-final-on-17-january/|title=Belgium: Eurosong 2016 final on 17 January|publisher=Esctoday.com|accessdate=3 January 2016|date=16 November 2015}}</ref> In the first show, she covered the song \"[[D\u00fcm Tek Tek]]\" by [[Hadise]], which represented Turkey in the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2009]].<ref>{{citeweb|url=http://deredactie.be/cm/vrtnieuws/cultuur%2Ben%2Bmedia/muziek/2.41904?eid=1.2537757|title=Amaryllis is alvast de lieveling van het publiek|publisher=Deredactie.be|last=Cardoen|first=Sandra|accessdate=3 January 2016|date=3 January 2016|language=Dutch}}</ref> In the second show she revealed her Eurovision candidate song \"[[What's the Pressure]]\", and received the highest televoting score.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hln.be/hln/nl/1326/Eurovisiesongfestival/article/detail/2580487/2016/01/10/Jury-euforisch-Vlaanderen-zou-zot-zijn-als-ze-Laura-Tesoro-niet-sturen.dhtml|title=Jury euforisch: \"Vlaanderen zou zot zijn, als ze Laura Tesoro niet sturen\"|publisher=[[Het Laatste Nieuws]]|website=hln.be|accessdate=10 January 2016|date=10 January 2016|language=Dutch}}</ref> In the final on 17 January 2016, she was declared the winner after placing first with both the Belgian public and international juries. She represented Belgium in the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2016]] in [[Stockholm]], where she placed tenth in the final.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eurovision.tv/page/news?id=belgium_laura_tesoro_wins_eurosong_2016|title=Belgium: Laura Tesoro wins Eurosong 2016!|date=17 January 2016|first=Escudero|last=Victor M.|publisher=EBU}}</ref> In the same year, Tesoro took part in the [[Flemish]] version of two animation movies: she first dubbed Poppy in [[DreamWorks Animation|DreamWorks]]' [[Trolls (film)|Trolls]]<ref name=\":0\" /> and later, Moana (known in Belgium as \"Vaiana\") in [[The Walt Disney Company|Disney]]'s [[Moana (2016 film)|movie of the same name]].<ref name=\":1\" /> On 28 April 2017, she released the single \"[[Higher (Laura Tesoro song)|Higher]]\", the song peaked at number 20 on the Flemish Singles Chart. Furthermore, on 27 October 2017, she released the single \"Beast\" which was available for pre-save on Spotify on 20 October, seven days prior.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://forms.sonymusicfans.com/LTPreSave/?ss=0|title=PRE-SAVE BEAST BY LAURA TESORO ON SPOTIFY|work=Sony Music Fans|access-date=29 October 2017|language=en}}</ref>\nShe is also a well-accomplished boxer, and her single \"Beast\" has a music video showing her boxing skills.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://forms.sonymusicfans.com/LTPreSave/?ss=0|title=PRE-SAVE BEAST BY LAURA TESORO ON SPOTIFY|work=Sony Music Fans|access-date=29 October 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n===Album===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:12em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:14em;\"| Details\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak chart positions\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Ultratop|BEL<br/>(Fl)]]<br/><ref name=\"FL\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ultratop.be/nl/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Laura+Tesoro|title=Discografie Laura Tesoro|publisher=Belgium (Flanders) Charts Portal. Hung Medien}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''Limits''\n|\n* Released: 24 October 2019<ref name=\"Limits\">{{cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/limits/1481780919|title=Limits by Laura Tesoro|website=[[Apple Music]]|accessdate=4 October 2019}}</ref>\n* Format: Digital download, CD\n* Label: [[Sony Music Entertainment]]\n| 3\n|}\n\n===Singles===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"4\"| Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Certifications\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Album\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Ultratop|BEL<br/>(Fl)]]<br/><ref name=\"FL\"/>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| [[\u00d63 Austria Top 40|AUT]]<br/><ref name=\"AUT\">{{cite web|url=http://austriancharts.at/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Laura+Tesoro|title=Discographie Laura Tesoro|publisher=Austrian Charts Portal. Hung Medien|accessdate=25 May 2016}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Syndicat National de l'\u00c9dition Phonographique|FRA]]<br/><ref name=\"FRA\">{{cite web|url=http://lescharts.com/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Laura+Tesoro|title=Discographie Laura Tesoro|publisher=French Charts Portal. Hung Medienn}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Sverigetopplistan|SWE]]<br/><ref name=\"SWE\">{{cite web|url=http://swedishcharts.com/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Laura+Tesoro|title=Discography Laura Tesoro|publisher=Swedish Charts Portal. Hung Medien}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[Outta Here (Laura Tesoro song)|Outta Here]]\"\n| 2014\n| 23 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| \n| rowspan=\"8\" {{n/a|Non-album singles}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[Funky Love (song)|Funky Love]]\"\n| 2015\n| \u2014{{efn|\"Funky Love\" did not enter the Ultratop 50, but peaked at number 27 on the Flemish [[Ultratop#Ultratip|Ultratip]] chart.}} || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| \n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[What's the Pressure]]\"\n| 2016\n| 2 || 75 || 103 || 82\n|\n* [[Belgian Entertainment Association|BEA]]: Gold\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[Higher (Laura Tesoro song)|Higher]]\"\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2017\n| 20 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Beast\"\n| 25 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Mutual\"\n| 2018\n| 23 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Up\"\n| rowspan=\"4\"| 2019\n| 34 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Thinking About You All the Time\" {{small|(live)}}\n| 44 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Limits\"\n| 35 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|\n| rowspan=\"2\"| ''Limits''<ref name=\"Limits\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[Press Pause (Laura Tesoro song)|Press Pause]]\"\n| 21 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| \n|-\n| colspan=\"20\" style=\"font-size:85%;\"| \"\u2014\" denotes a single that did not chart or were not released.\n|}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Award\n! Category\n! Result\n|-\n|2016\n| [[2016 MTV Europe Music Awards|MTV Europe Music Awards]]\n| Best Belgian Act\n| {{nom}}\n|}\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n!Title\n!Role\n!Notes\n|-\n| 2008\n|''[[Witse]]''\n|Evy Cuypers\n|Episode: \"Innige band\"\n|-\n| 2012\u201314\n|''[[Familie]]''\n|Charlotte Kennis\n|73 episodes\n|-\n| 2015\n|''Altijd prijs''\n|Julie Aerts\n|3 episodes\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2016\n|''[[Trolls (film)|Trolls]]''\n|Poppy<ref name=\":0\">{{Citation|last=FoxFilmBelgium|title=Trolls {{!}} Interview Laura Tesoro {{!}} HD {{!}} Vlaams {{!}} 2016|date=14 October 2016|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Om8L4lYIgh0|accessdate=1 November 2016}}</ref>\n| rowspan=\"3\" |[[Flemish language|Flemish]] version\n|-\n|''[[Moana (2016 film)|Moana]]''\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Moana (Disney)|Moana]]<ref name=\":1\">{{Citation|last=Disney Belgi\u00eb|title=Laura Tesoro is de Vlaamse Stem van Vaiana {{!}} Disney BE|date=31 October 2016|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0B204ZgANIY|accessdate=1 November 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://disneyinternationalvoices.weebly.com/moana--vaiana.html|title=Moana / Vaiana|website=CHARGUIGOU|language=fr|access-date=2019-05-31}}</ref>\n|-\n|2018\n|''[[Ralph Breaks the Internet]]''\n|-\n| 2019\n|''Studio Tarara''\n|Dancer 1\n|Episode: \"1.4\"\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n\n===Notes===\n{{Reflist|group=lower-alpha}}\n\n===Sources===\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Instagram|lauratesoro}}\n*{{IMDB name|nm3128783}}\n{{Commons category|Laura Tesoro}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{succession box\n| before=[[Lo\u00efc Nottet]]<br>with \"[[Rhythm Inside (Lo\u00efc Nottet song)|Rhythm Inside]]\"\n| title=[[Belgium in the Eurovision Song Contest]]\n| years=[[Eurovision Song Contest 2016|2016]]\n| after=[[Blanche (singer)|Blanche]]<br>with \"[[City Lights (Blanche song)|City Lights]]\"\n}}\n{{s-end}}\n{{Belgium in the Eurovision Song Contest |state=autocollapse}}\n{{Eurovision Song Contest 2016 |state=autocollapse}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Tesoro, Laura}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1996 births]]\n[[Category:Belgian female pop singers]]\n[[Category:Belgian Eurovision Song Contest entrants]]\n[[Category:Eurovision Song Contest entrants of 2016]]\n[[Category:Belgian people of Italian descent]]\n[[Category:English-language singers from Belgium]]\n[[Category:Flemish stage actresses]]\n[[Category:Belgian child actresses]]\n[[Category:Flemish television actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century Flemish actresses]]\n[[Category:The Voice (franchise) contestants]]\n[[Category:Flemish musicians]]\n[[Category:21st-century Belgian singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century women singers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2017}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name                = Laura Tesoro\n| image               = ESC2016 - Belgium Meet & Greet 14 (crop).jpg\n| caption             = Tesoro in 2016\n| image_size          = <!-- Only for images narrower than 220 pixels -->\n| background          = solo_singer\n| birth_name          =\n| alias               = \n| birth_date          = {{birth date and age|1996|8|19|df=yes}}\n| birth_place         = [[Antwerp]], Belgium\n| origin              = \n| instrument          = Vocals\n| genre               = {{hlist|[[Pop music|Pop]]|[[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]|[[Funk music|funk]]|[[Dance music|dance]]}}\n| occupation          = {{hlist|Singer|actress}}\n| years_active        = 2008\u2013present\n| label               =\n| associated_acts     = {{hlist|[[Koen Wauters]]}}\n| website             = \n}}\n\n'''Laura Tesoro''' (born 19 August 1996) is a Belgian singer and actress. She represented [[Belgium in the Eurovision Song Contest 2016]] with the song \"[[What's the Pressure]]\".  Tesoro is also known for portraying Charlotte on the Flemish soap opera ''[[Familie]]'', and placing second on [[The Voice van Vlaanderen (season 3)|season three]] of ''[[The Voice van Vlaanderen]]''. The singer is also one of the four coaches on ''[[The Voice Kids (Belgian TV series))]]''\n\n==Biography==\n\n===1996\u20132014: Early life and career beginnings===\nTesoro was born on 19 August 1996 in [[Antwerp]] to an Italian father and a Belgian mother.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://mobile.twitter.com/Lauwraaaaah_/status/563378079004131328?p=v|title= I am Belgian but my father is Italian|accessdate= 9 March 2016|author= Tesoro, Laura|date= 5 February 2015|publisher= [[Twitter]]}}</ref> She had her first acting role in the Flemish crime drama ''[[Witse]]'' as Evy Cuypers in 2008, and went on to perform in musicals such as ''[[Annie (musical)|Annie]]'' and ''Domino''. She performed at [[Ketnetpop]] in 2009. From 2012 to 2014, she appeared as Charlotte in ''[[Familie]]'', a love interest to Guido. In 2014 she appeared in [[The Voice van Vlaanderen (season 3)|season three]] of ''[[The Voice van Vlaanderen]]'', where she ended up as the runner-up. Throughout her time on the show, she was a member of Team [[Koen Wauters|Koen]]. She released her debut single \"[[Outta Here (Laura Tesoro song)|Outta Here]]\" the same year, which peaked at number 23 on the Belgian Flemish Singles Chart.\n\n===2015\u2013present: Eurovision Song Contest===\n{{Main|Belgium in the Eurovision Song Contest 2016}}\nIn 2015, she released her second single \"[[Funky Love (song)|Funky Love]]\". In November 2015, Tesoro was announced as one of the five participants of [[Belgium in the Eurovision Song Contest 2016|''Eurosong 2016'']].<ref>{{citeweb|first=Gil|last=Laufer|url=http://esctoday.com/106766/belgium-national-final-on-17-january/|title=Belgium: Eurosong 2016 final on 17 January|publisher=Esctoday.com|accessdate=3 January 2016|date=16 November 2015}}</ref> In the first show, she covered the song \"[[D\u00fcm Tek Tek]]\" by [[Hadise]], which represented Turkey in the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2009]].<ref>{{citeweb|url=http://deredactie.be/cm/vrtnieuws/cultuur%2Ben%2Bmedia/muziek/2.41904?eid=1.2537757|title=Amaryllis is alvast de lieveling van het publiek|publisher=Deredactie.be|last=Cardoen|first=Sandra|accessdate=3 January 2016|date=3 January 2016|language=Dutch}}</ref> In the second show she revealed her Eurovision candidate song \"[[What's the Pressure]]\", and received the highest televoting score.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hln.be/hln/nl/1326/Eurovisiesongfestival/article/detail/2580487/2016/01/10/Jury-euforisch-Vlaanderen-zou-zot-zijn-als-ze-Laura-Tesoro-niet-sturen.dhtml|title=Jury euforisch: \"Vlaanderen zou zot zijn, als ze Laura Tesoro niet sturen\"|publisher=[[Het Laatste Nieuws]]|website=hln.be|accessdate=10 January 2016|date=10 January 2016|language=Dutch}}</ref> In the final on 17 January 2016, she was declared the winner after placing first with both the Belgian public and international juries. She represented Belgium in the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2016]] in [[Stockholm]], where she placed tenth in the final.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eurovision.tv/page/news?id=belgium_laura_tesoro_wins_eurosong_2016|title=Belgium: Laura Tesoro wins Eurosong 2016!|date=17 January 2016|first=Escudero|last=Victor M.|publisher=EBU}}</ref> In the same year, Tesoro took part in the [[Flemish]] version of two animation movies: she first dubbed Poppy in [[DreamWorks Animation|DreamWorks]]' [[Trolls (film)|Trolls]]<ref name=\":0\" /> and later, Moana (known in Belgium as \"Vaiana\") in [[The Walt Disney Company|Disney]]'s [[Moana (2016 film)|movie of the same name]].<ref name=\":1\" /> On 28 April 2017, she released the single \"[[Higher (Laura Tesoro song)|Higher]]\", the song peaked at number 20 on the Flemish Singles Chart. Furthermore, on 27 October 2017, she released the single \"Beast\" which was available for pre-save on Spotify on 20 October, seven days prior.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://forms.sonymusicfans.com/LTPreSave/?ss=0|title=PRE-SAVE BEAST BY LAURA TESORO ON SPOTIFY|work=Sony Music Fans|access-date=29 October 2017|language=en}}</ref>\nShe is also a well-accomplished boxer, and her single \"Beast\" has a music video showing her boxing skills.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://forms.sonymusicfans.com/LTPreSave/?ss=0|title=PRE-SAVE BEAST BY LAURA TESORO ON SPOTIFY|work=Sony Music Fans|access-date=29 October 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n===Album===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:12em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:14em;\"| Details\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak chart positions\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Ultratop|BEL<br/>(Fl)]]<br/><ref name=\"FL\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ultratop.be/nl/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Laura+Tesoro|title=Discografie Laura Tesoro|publisher=Belgium (Flanders) Charts Portal. Hung Medien}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''Limits''\n|\n* Released: 24 October 2019<ref name=\"Limits\">{{cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/limits/1481780919|title=Limits by Laura Tesoro|website=[[Apple Music]]|accessdate=4 October 2019}}</ref>\n* Format: Digital download, CD\n* Label: [[Sony Music Entertainment]]\n| 3\n|}\n\n===Singles===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"4\"| Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Certifications\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Album\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Ultratop|BEL<br/>(Fl)]]<br/><ref name=\"FL\"/>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| [[\u00d63 Austria Top 40|AUT]]<br/><ref name=\"AUT\">{{cite web|url=http://austriancharts.at/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Laura+Tesoro|title=Discographie Laura Tesoro|publisher=Austrian Charts Portal. Hung Medien|accessdate=25 May 2016}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Syndicat National de l'\u00c9dition Phonographique|FRA]]<br/><ref name=\"FRA\">{{cite web|url=http://lescharts.com/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Laura+Tesoro|title=Discographie Laura Tesoro|publisher=French Charts Portal. Hung Medienn}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Sverigetopplistan|SWE]]<br/><ref name=\"SWE\">{{cite web|url=http://swedishcharts.com/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Laura+Tesoro|title=Discography Laura Tesoro|publisher=Swedish Charts Portal. Hung Medien}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[Outta Here (Laura Tesoro song)|Outta Here]]\"\n| 2014\n| 23 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| \n| rowspan=\"8\" {{n/a|Non-album singles}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[Funky Love (song)|Funky Love]]\"\n| 2015\n| \u2014{{efn|\"Funky Love\" did not enter the Ultratop 50, but peaked at number 27 on the Flemish [[Ultratop#Ultratip|Ultratip]] chart.}} || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n| \n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[What's the Pressure]]\"\n| 2016\n| 2 || 75 |